overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of their sleep questionnaire
  application, seeking to validate its adherence to the provided acceptance
  criteria and to implement any identified missing functionalities. The agent
  conducted a thorough code review, identified several gaps, and formulated a
  detailed action plan. Subsequently, the agent proceeded to implement key
  features. This included integrating a 1-10 severity scale for tiredness,
  complete with critical safety warnings, and developing robust detection and
  recommendation logic for both Comorbid Insomnia and Sleep Apnea (COMISA) and
  Insufficient Sleep Syndrome. Additionally, a dedicated "Resources & Next
  Steps" section was added to the report, featuring placeholder outbound links
  to relevant sleep and mental health resources. The agent also enhanced the
  Excessive Daytime Sleepiness (EDS) scoring by implementing a weighted system,
  providing a more nuanced assessment of severity. Each change involved
  modifications across multiple files, including type definitions, validation
  schemas, UI components, and PDF generation logic.
